{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 16:07:49.089336", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nOverview\\n- Topology: 2-tier Clos with EBGP across leaves, spines, and a super-spine. Each leaf advertises its directly connected /24 host subnet (10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24) into BGP. Hosts: pc_0_0 (to leaf_router_0_0) and pc_0_1 (to leaf_router_0_1).\\n\\nKey Symptoms Observed\\n- pc_0_0 → pc_0_1 ping: Network is unreachable.\\n- pc_0_1 → pc_0_0 ping (by name): Temporary failure in name resolution (host has no IP configured; not a fabric issue).\\n- pc_0_1 → 10.0.1.1 (its default gateway on leaf_router_0_1): OK.\\n- pc_0_1 → 10.0.0.1 (leaf_router_0_0 SVI in the other subnet): OK.\\n\\nControl Plane (BGP) Health\\n- All BGP adjacencies across leaves, spines, and super-spine are Established with non-zero prefixes received.\\n  - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200): 4 neighbors up; connected 10.0.0.0/24; BGP routes for 10.0.1.0/24 and others via spines.\\n  - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201): 4 neighbors up; connected 10.0.1.0/24; BGP routes for 10.0.0.0/24 and others via spines.\\n  - spine_router_0_0 and spine_router_0_1: All leaf and super-spine peerings up; have BGP routes to both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24.\\n  - super_spine_router_0 (AS 65000): All spine peerings up; has BGP routes to both leaf subnets.\\n- Routing tables on all routers include the expected /24 host networks, with next-hops pointing correctly towards the respective leaves/spines.\\n- No signs of BGP session flap or convergence issues; RIB counts and PfxRcd are consistent for this lab.\\n\\nData Plane Observations\\n- leaf_router_0_1 eth4 (10.0.1.1/24) shows traffic consistent with pings from pc_0_1.\\n- leaf_router_0_0 eth4 (10.0.0.1/24) shows 0 RX/TX packets, indicating no traffic from the attached host link, consistent with a host-side issue.\\n\\nHost-Side State\\n- pc_0_1: Properly configured\\n  - IP: 10.0.1.2/24, default via 10.0.1.1\\n  - Can reach its gateway (10.0.1.1) and the other leaf’s SVI (10.0.0.1) through the fabric.\\n- pc_0_0: Misconfigured\\n  - Only loopback present; no eth0 with IP; no routes.\\n  - As a result, pc_0_0 cannot originate traffic to the fabric (Network is unreachable).\\n\\nAnomalies Identified\\n- pc_0_0 lacks any L3 configuration on its host interface toward leaf_router_0_0:\\n  - No IP on eth0 (expected to be in 10.0.0.0/24).\\n  - No default route.\\n  - Corroborated by zero traffic on leaf_router_0_0 eth4 (10.0.0.1/24).\\n\\nFault Localization\\n- Faulty device: pc_0_0 (the host).\\n- Fabric devices (leaf_router_0_0, leaf_router_0_1, spine_router_0_0, spine_router_0_1, super_spine_router_0): Operating normally with healthy BGP and correct routing.\\n\\nRoot Cause\\n- Host-side misconfiguration on pc_0_0: the interface connected to leaf_router_0_0 is not configured with an IP address in 10.0.0.0/24 (and has no default route). This prevents end-to-end host connectivity, despite a healthy EBGP fabric., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='16770f1a-19e9-4f91-9030-c5c530361c37'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
